  Be sure that you have an application to open
  this file type before downloading and/or purchasing.
608 KB|2 pagesProduct DescriptionSeparate files for electronic postings are included! Including separate fillable pdf files for student answers and e-submission!

This one page reading plus one page of questions summarizes the end of the Ottoman Empire and the establishment of the Republic of Turkey during the "Between the Wars" era. It chronicles the rise of the Young Turks and the leadership of Mustafa Kemal Ataturk. This is designed for middle school or high school students. The reading is visually appealing and broken into chunks. It can be used for classwork, homework, research or as a platform for projects. Questions are content based and designed to target essential content acquisition. If interested in similar readings on the "Between the Wars" era, check other offerings by this author. A set of 10 readings is available as a Between the Wars Unit (plus lesson suggestions). *PLEASE NOTE: This product is not modifiable.

